==Latin==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[νόμισμα]]''' (''nomisma'') "current coin, custom", from '''[[νομίζω]]''' (''nomizo'') "to hold or own as a custom, usage, to use customarily, practise, to be used to a thing", hence "to make common use of", from '''[[νόμος]]''' (''nomos'') "usage, custom".

===Noun===
'''nomisma''' (''genitive'' '''[[nomismatis]]'''); {{n}}, ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|third declension]]''

# [[coin]]
# [[image]] on a coin

